gm-plugkit in-process learning API (gm-plugkit/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js): export async createPlugkit({wasmPath?,fresh?}) returns {dispatch(verb,body)->parsedJSON, version(), _instance}. Caches one wasm instance process-wide (singleton unless opts.fresh). The wrapper is ESM (import.meta); its trailing IIFE is guarded by _isCliEntry (path.resolve(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url))===path.resolve(process.argv[1])) so `node wrapper.js spool` still runs the daemon but `await import('gm-plugkit/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js')` does NOT auto-run. dispatch reuses dispatchVerbToWasmInternal (alloc/dispatch_verb/free). Verbs memorize-fire / recall / auto-recall run in-process. The wasm host functions resolve .gm/rs-learn.db from CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR||cwd of the HOST process, so set cwd/CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR before first dispatch so memories land in the project .gm, not the gm-tools install dir. First dispatch cold-loads wasm + BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5 embed model (~133MB safetensors) so instantiate lazily off the hot path. index.js is CommonJS so consume the wrapper file directly via dynamic import, not via require('gm-plugkit'). This is how freddie makes gm rs-learn its primary learning mechanism in-process.